Ideals__c: Co-develop an as a service proposition that can be resold to institutional clients
Mutual_Plan__c: Being developed with MSFT and LSEG
Compelling_Events__c: CIO/COO looking for proposal by mid September as basis for board presentation in mid October
Vision__c: Trade/Market Surveillance solution with GTM proposition
Current_Situation__c: LSE are looking to enhance their current post trade surveillance capabilities to improve overall performance and to develop a proposition that can be taken to market as an as a service offering .
Action_Plan__c:
4/8 - Liam Smith to facilitate intro to his boss Nikhil Rathi CEO of LSE for further discussion on progressing surveillance opportunity in parallel with wider strategic LSEG play being led by Manoj.  Liam feels the initiative is being lost and has requested CS support to progress the discussion within his line of business.
3/29 - Meeting with Liam Smith deferred to Friday this week. Next steps to be agreed at this meeting.
3/20 - Deal is now linked to wider strategic discussions with Tom, Greg and the analytics team.  Rich K leading dialogue to build out understanding of ISD2.0 agenda so that commercials can be aligned.  Follow up meeting with Liam Smith scheduled for this week to align on specifics for surveillance.
3/15 - Interlock and discovery sessions with Tom Gywdr (CIO) and Greg Allen (CTO) pending.  Also need to engage new Head of Analytics to align around SAP HANA.  Manoj/Rich pitch to Chris Corrado has driven significant interest but has pushed out timeline and ETA to conclude the strategic deal until Q2 earliest.
3/5 - Rich K and Manoj working on new framework for strategic approach at LSEG.  View from Chris Corrado via Manoj is that surveillance only approach won't fly and any deal needs to be connected to strategic re-platforming for data and analytics.  Manoj vision needs a lot of work on way to next steering meeting on 4/11.
2/26- Internal CS review required.  Manoj "big deal" initiative impacting timeline on any decision making over this initiative.  Initial understanding of the ask is to run an intensive strategic consulting engagement that is not aligned with current engagement approach.  This requires broad CS exec alignment to define objectives, success criteria, resources and scope of proposal before any further qualification of the potential opportunity can take place.
2/18 - Exec playback went well with Chris Corrado.  Some refinement required to the content that will be completed over next 2 weeks with a view to engaging David Schwimmer (CEO) in late February to discuss funding going forward.
2/4 - Exec playback on engagement to date with Chris Corrado (CIO/COO) and Liam Smith (Head of Surveillance) plus Manoj and ML set for today.  Next steps and funding to be discussed and timing to be agreed for proposed next steps.
1/21 - AIC proposal submitted for review with Liam Smith at final playback of current engagement.  Looking for budgetary qualification to proceed with next steps to focus on one of the six suggested entry points for the surveillance service.  Bob G and Rick K attending playback.  Matt W on leave next week.
1/14 - Next steps pending next playback with Liam Smith (Hof Market Surveillance) and team. SoW revision required to take engagement to conclusion by end January.
1/7 - Client interlock scheduled with Ash Rautela, Project manager, to understand how current SoW closes out and how engagement relates to strategic investment plans within LSEG.  No accountable exec is a major issue not yet addressed by Chris Corrado and team.  Current SoW will be extended to Jan 31st to aid qualification in or out.
12/17 - Based on checkpoint with Chris Corrado (CIO) and CS team next steps and further funding to be agreed thru end January.
12/10 - After significant refocus on the current engagement to address the broader scope of the service proposition we have paused the current engagement to prepare for a playback on 12/10. This will also be aligned with bringing Manoj and Chris Corrado up to date on the expansion of scope to cover a much broader consulting engagement which goes well beyond the feasibility scope currently defined in the existing SoW.
11/26 - Requalifying scope and approach for engagement.  Further discussion on longer term investment is dependent on defining value and success criteria from current feasibility assessment.
11/15 - Reengaging on strategic investment in AIC assuming successful outcome of Phase 0.  Matt W to follow up with Manoj to get commitment from Chris Corrado CIO/COO
11/9 - On hold pending progress on Phase 0. AIC construct shared with LSEG procurement for parallel review with delivery of Phase 0.
8/29 - Development of outline PoV underway for validation with client SMEs.  The PoV will drive scope and approach for inclusion in the proposal due toward end of August. Commercial work stream running in parallel with both MSFT and LSEG procurement.
8/22 - Progressing LSEG procurement discussions to agree on boarding process for CogScale.  In parallel we are progressing on boarding for CogScale as MSFT subcontractor to allow us to formally engage in PoC delivery. Info sec discussions ongoing to define secure Azure environment to land client data.  Top down PoV development on Market/Trade surveillance underway for playback to Kaushy (Lead on Quantitative Surveillance) on 8/22 and to prepare input for client workshop in early September when Liam Smith (Head of Market Surveillance) returns from leave.
8/13 - Infosec have pushed back on MSFT and CS due to lack of clarity on design for Azure hosted secure environment for data to be transferred to.  The generic nature of the response does not meet the clients requirements. Next step is for a combined MSFT, LSEG (Cloud Team) and CS group to work through a proposed design.  This has not been helped by slippage on the Azure signing and lack of internal LSEG experience on Azure.
7/31 - Info sec sessions with MSFT, Bridgeweave to be completed. NDAs returned by :LSEG and then data transfer by week of 8/6. Formal workshop will be wk comm 8/13
7/25 Planning review session with MSFT and LSEG to discuss data access and agree next steps - however this is dependent on NDAs being put in place with CS and Bridgeweave in advance of this date, otherwise the timeline will slip.
7/17 MSFT driving info sec discussion so that assessment phase can take place based on high level data discovery. Expecting follow up with Liam Smith, Product Owner, next week.
7/9 Mobilisation with MSFT underway.  Aman Kohli at MSFT engaging to drive dates and structure of initial steps towards proposal with Liam Smith at LSEG.  CogSCale engaging with Liam on NDAs and will also support infosec sessions proposed over coming week.
6/18 Chris Corrado (CIO) has introduced us to Ann Neidenbach (Head of Shared Services) and Liam Smith (Product Manager, Market Surveillance) to Bob G.  Discovery meeting scheduled.  Parallel dialogue with Microsoft this week to agree interlock and next steps with client.

- define respective scoping and resourcing for a jointly proposed and delivered Privacy Protection Platform  (CCPA) solution, leveraging Capgemini's existing CCPA solution framework modified to leverage our Profile-of-1 capability. 
- negotiate revenue sharing with Cap (against available budget and total proposal cost)
- build and deliver a joint proposal for a Privacy Protection solution, along with a milestone and follow on projects 12-24 month "draft roadmap" for CLR Cognitive Capability Transformation.
Additionally, our scope needs to include a one-time use case project for automated analysis, tagging and routing of approximately 1M documents currently housed in a Documentum Platform that need to migrated to newly acquired WORM storage. 12.6 Prep call with IBM
Here's the info on the 12/15 Lane Bryant mtg:
- we met w/CMO, SVP, Store Ops, VP, IT + others to visit their new 'Lane Style Studio' (LSS) pilot concept in Oct. 
- LSS is an in store personal styling capability/space they''ll be rolling out to limited stores (you make an appointment, a stylist picks out outfits for you after listening to your tastes, color preferences, style/fit preferences, etc - she makes a personal connection to gain credibility/trust.)
- Initial results in first 8 weeks: sales 300% of bau sales
- they've asked IBM to come in and highlight a few things:  
1. how we could operationalize the in-store experience (better mobile app w/back end connections to CRM, scheduling, KPI measurements, etc.)
2. their ultimate goal is to bring this to the digital channel (only way to scale and only way to get at more digitally engaged/focused demographic.) - CS piece
Update from Beth Ellis - L Brands - good mtg w/Chief Data Officer/Scientist, Heather Wilson - she wants to meet w/our Sr Execs (Bob Picciano, etc.) to discuss agenda for Watson session (she's used to working w/Sr IBM execs from her days at AIG.)  Once agenda confirmed, I planned to have you part of the session (TBD).  Also discussed ideas w/their Tech Innovation Director, Jason Harrell (he's responsible for quick proof concepts w/the business.)  He wants something very specific around 'fit' for sales associates (consistent process) and digital channel but he's not responding to my emails after first (impromptu) mtg - working w/Nanda to bug him.

Name: Maplin Engage - SaaS - Production
Mutual_Plan__c: IBM are defocussing on cognitive with this customer
Current_Situation__c: Stalled due to new CIO taking over
Next_Step__c: Monitor via IBM for potential to revisit with CIO
Action_Plan__c:
2/21 Mukul Dixit advised that due to change in CIO at Maplin it is now very unlikely that the CogScale component of the SAP Hybris release will be implemented. There are various political issues on the account now the new CIO has taken over and IBM are not confident that they can get cognitive back on the executive priority list. We agreed that our attention needs to focus on other more receptive clients as there is not sufficient value in the current solution to enable us to push this initiative back up the priority list with the new exec team. New CIO is very focussed on moving to in house build model and has added over 50 new IT staff in a move away from supplier developed capabilities - IBM unsure of overall impact on their position on the account.
2/20 Meeting with Mukul today to discuss next steps. Updated to follow.
2/3 - Meeting with Mukul to discuss Maplin has been scheduled for 2/20. Bob G and Matt W will attend to agree plan to move Maplin to production and client engagement.

1/27 - Meeting with Mukul, Adrian and Dan this week to discuss progress on Apparel Showcase and also to agree next steps on Maplin.  Mukul is not available for 2 weeks to discuss Maplin - working to lock down date with him later in the month.  Apparel showcase sign off to be agreed today 1/27 - next step is to agree how we use partner cloud going forward.

1.20 Next steps - Meeting set with Mukul Dixit and team to discuss current release status and to plan how we move the CS element into production in Q1. Plan to engage Maplin directly to be agreed on 1/23.

1/12 - Maplin P1 work has been moved out of Partner Cloud while SAP release is finalised. Agreement with IBM (Nancy and Mukul)  is that the Apparel Showcase will be built in the Partner Cloud, while Maplin plans are finalised, to allow Mukul's team to develop their GTM showcase for Cog Scale for broader retail opportunities. Currently the Showcase build is going well and CS have delivered into the IBM tech team. Next step is to agree sign off criteria for the Apparel build - intent is that this work should be completed by end January latest.  Adrian, Maria and Mukul at IBM need to be engaged week commencing 1/16 to agree the sign off steps. Matt W engaged with Trent and Dan Sheard at IBM to track progress on weekly basis.

12/12 - IBM have advised (Mukul Dixit  - Europe SAP/Hybris Practice Lead) that Maplin release will be delayed until early 2017 due to wider SAP rollout dependency.  Cog Scale development has gone through initial test but now needs end to end testing with IBM delivered front end. No further updates anticipated until early/mid January.

11/25 - IBM have advised that they are not in a position to move forward with combined delivery into test with Maplin and it is now unlikely to happen until early 2017 due to other commitments from a Hybris delivery perspective and busy period for Maplin.  Proposal is to take Engage out of partner cloud until IBM ready to move forward and to redeploy partner cloud and associated resources to build out an end to end recommendation engine demo to underpin broader GTM plan.  This is in discussion and needs approvals by CS team and IBM partner cloud owner.  Meeting Mukul Dixit on 11/25 to discuss further. Critical next step is to present to new CIO and platform owner with support from IBM


11/21 - Delivery checkpoint discussion due to review status on delivery of a testable capability by the internal team. Sunil, Bob and Trent in discussion with Gopal. 

10/27 - A number of threads of activity are in plan 
1) Complete Maplin build and start an internal test 
2) Move to integration test and user testing phase with IBM and Maplin
3) Gain feedback from client on validity and value of solution


Have moved Maplin to DEcember, due to IBM SAP implementation being delayed.  Next step is 1) gain testing plan with IBM; 2) gain testing plan with Maplin; 3) put proposal in front of Maplin for SaaS deal. 

Maplin prototype in Partner Garage is progressing.  Hopefully we can deliver something that they desire to take to production.  Guessing a 100k deal, perhaps large if we can extend the term to 3-5 years.  

8.3  - Client's existing digital transformation work is taking precedent and they are delivering a new search capability. Whilst they are committed to Cognitive, they are looking for a Q1 2017 go live. They have no interest in the short term for funding a piece of work. We will revisit this again in Q3 2016. 
IBM will look to build a html mock up for Sapphire - we can do a very lightweight touch of this - not really anything we want to do. No funding agreed through the IBM account team as yet. 


22-G+Feb. agree on scope with IBMUK.  Sunil driving with local IBM team to gain agreement on use case.  idea is to Daniel Sherd is part of the IBM SAP Hybris team and assigned to Maplin.  We've asked to meet directly with the client.
Problems_Impacts__c: Cognitive is not on new CIO priority list - lots of focus to moving from supplier build to infuse build
Decision_Making_Process__c: IBM are not supporting moving this forward

Current_Situation__c: Complex and inefficient internal buying process
Next_Step__c: IBM finalising SoW with VPC for Phase Zero work to start in June
Action_Plan__c:
9/14 VPC esignature still not received on SoW. Chasing daily. VPC have confirmed it is in process and all approvals have been received.
8/14 VPC have sighed IBM SoW, awaiting IBM Workorder for partner cloud.  Client kick off meeting scheduled for 8/16 to agree engagement plan. Avi leading. Awaiting delivery resource assignment from Paul H.
8/7 Awaiting signature from VPC on IBM SoW. Slipped again based on latest update from Julian Trent.
8/3 IBM advising they expect client sign off on SoW this week. 
7/24 Follow up call with Julian Trent at IBM planned.  Julian and team are progressing with final clarifications on SoW however they continue to miss dates and fail to conclude the final approvals with Vodafone.  Avi supporting IBM with rapid responses and follow up however we are in a holding pattern.
7/12 R-engaging to discuss final changes to SoW on basis VPC will sign with IBM by mid month.
6/30 Assuming deal lost by IBM. Will update SF record by end of month if no further update received.
6/23 VPC and IBM missed yet another update commitment to advise on go/no go decision. Chased Julian Trent on 6/16 but no response.
6/15 Pedro Barata confirmed today (6/10) to Matt W directly that a decision will be taken by mid next week by key stakeholders on go no go for the Phase Zero work.
6/8 Deal at risk due to IBM losing control of the commercial discussion with stakeholders.  Pedro Barata advised one key stakeholder out of office however there is now a risk VPC may not go ahead with this initiative. Expect follow up next week from Pedro.
5/29 Pushed CBA SoW back to all IBM stakeholders and restated that having the partner cloud secured is fundamental to the CS component of the commercial proposal tabled with VPC.  Waiting for IBM to respond on this and confirm their decision based on risk to their overall proposition of not having a signed agreement in place.
5/22 Julian Trent at IBM has advised that a call has been scheduled between Bob Murphy (IBM CPO) and Ninian Wilson (VPC CPO) to unblock the sign off on the SoW and accurate engagement. Matt and Julian to connect on 5/22 to discuss outcome of exec call.
5/16 Pushing for call with client and IBM to finalise remaining questions on SoW.  Attended call with IBM on 5/11 and pushing for joint engagement following that discussion.  Lack of responsiveness from Julian needs escalating as we cannot continue to work with Vodafone in this way.
5/12 Follow up with julian Trent to push for closure on open SoW questions from client.
5/8 Call set with IBM to review feedback from Vodafone on the IBM SoW - Avi will lead from CS however primary questions are IBMs to address.
5/2 Sow now sent to Vodafone by IBM (issued 4/26) Matt W and Avi to follow up with Julian Trent, Graham Wright at IBM re dates and resources needed to kick off in May.
4/24 Matt W will ollow up with Julian Trent at IBM as soon as he returns to office. Have spoken to Vodafone who have advised SoW has still not been released to them for review.  Pedro Barata will need at least a week to progress SoW approval once he receives it from IBM.
Next step - call with Julian Trent for 4/19 to confirm status on SoW release.  Following that we will set project planning meeting with Avi and Gopal.
4/14 Set opportunity value to zero $ as this is proposed to go in to current partner cloud with no additional revenue from IBM for initial Phase Zero work.  Phase 1 will be chargeable for Q3. Next step - IBM to release SoW to Vodafone expected 4/13 but no confirmation yet this has happened. Julian Trent advised final internal contracts still to be completed within Watson and GBS.
4/6 Matt followed up with Pedro Barata (Cog Procurement Programme Mgt) he still has not received the IBM SoW but will advised as soon as he does.  Matt W to keep chasing.
4/5 - Update - Kathleen (IBM) says SOW is expected to be in Vodafone's hands tomorrow (4/6)

3/30 - UPDATE (Gailey) IBM will not sign CS SOW until Vodafone signs IBM's SOW for Phase 0 Partner Cloud.  Julian/Graham will be in USA (NC) Mon/Tues - Mudd joining them  - Bill Z expects CS SOW signed 'next week' 

3/24 IBM SoW to Vodafone has been approved by Watson Group.  This is now with Christine Wyatt, GBS GPS Leader for sign off as IBM approver.  Chris will also sign the CS to IBM Workorder for Partner Cloud.  High risk on current timeline that IBM will not secure signatures within Qtr.  Julian Trent and Graham Wright at IBM have lines into Chris.  Next Step - Chad G or Bob H to put a call in to Chris to see if we can ensure release to client today.
3/17 Phase Zero partner cloud SoW finalised with IBM on 3/16.  Working on concluding Watson Group sign off review so SoW can be released to Vodafone by 3/20.  Julian Trent at IBM is managing release process to Pedro Barata at VPC. Chad Avi and Matt will managed process to set up IBM to CS work request following VPC review. Target is 3/27 for backing off both agreements.

3/3 IBM have released the draft SoW today for CS review and comment.  Intent is to present the SoW to Pedro Barata (Cog Prog Manager) week commencing 3/6. Matt W and Pascal to lead on final review and comments. Julian Trent will present back to Vodafone before end end of the week.
2/24 Great workshop with Pedro, Kate and IBM yesterday.  Kate is keen to progress with the Phase Zero proposal put forward by IBM to build out the demonstrator in the partner cloud using VF data.  IBM/CS to finalise SoW and share with Pedro and Kate by 2/28.  Review of SoW to be finalised by end of week with a view to being in position to sign the SoW by 3/15 latest.  Kate needs to identify her user group to support the initiative, and agree sample data set and specific category to focus on. Target is for work to start late March and run for 10-12 weeks under the SoW.

2/23 Design Thinking Workshop with Pedro Barata (Vodafone Procurement Business Owner) and Kate Watterson (Vodafone Simplification Project Lead) - being delivered in partnership with IBM. Pascal D and Julian Trent from IBM facilitating.
2/22 Finalise SoW with IBM to present to VPC on 2/23

Decision_Making_Process__c: Demonstrator to be built with IBM support - 3 month SoW

1/20 - This week spent with Rich K and Pascal D agreeing all technical artefacts required to initiate due diligence phase with IBM.  Progress has been slowed due to conflicts with Barclays work. Hold on confirming follow up dates to Vodafone and IBM until we have a clear plan and dates agreed internally.  1/17 call with Pedro Barata and his two category managers on other CS client successes went well. 1/11 - Agreed action plan with IBM, John White (VPC Partner and Opportunity Owner) and Julian Trent (Procurement SME) for joint close plan on CCA. Introduced Shay and Gopal. Next meeting will be 1/17 with Pedro and category managers. Assuming we tick this box we can move into working joint commercials with IBM for a Feb close.

1/3 - Reviewed commercial feedback from Pedro Barata this week.  We have now begun to exchange drafts on key commercial principles.  Awaiting comments back from category managers week of 1/9.  Next step agreed as presentation of success stories on 1/17 - pushing  for face to face visit to Lux but this is yet to be confirmed.  Interlock meeting with IBM team (Julian Trent and John White) scheduled for 1/11 to intro Shay and to ensure we are fully aligned on sales strategy.  There remains open issue around what IBM response will be in the event Vodafone decide they do not want to contract on blue paper.

12/16 - Met with Pedro Barata this week by Video Conf to agree next meeting with category managers 12/20. Pedro is looking for over CS success stories to be presented.  Following this there will be a commercial review and a followup demo on insights lifecycle to complete prior to any decision being made in January 17.  CS need to align with IBM post 12/20 to start work on commercial model and backing off licensing, services etc.

12/8 - Pedro Barata (Programme Manager) has not yet responded regarding key meeting due to be scheduled with category managers to review insights lifecycle demo and other Cog Scale use cases. Expected session to be on 12/14 however this will now be rescheduled due to resources on both sides being committed elsewhere.
12/1  - Vodafone advised that no decision will be taken on moving into phase 1 until January 17. Due to open commercial questions, lack of stakeholder and exec availability and need to align contractual construct with IBM this will move in to new year. MoU proposed but declined by Pedro Barata. Priority item to address is insight lifecycle workshop.  CS to progress backing off license terms with IBM reseller agreement in readiness for close in Jan.

11/25 - Awaiting feedback from IBM meeting with Pedro and VPC CFO in Luxembourg on 11/24. Julian Trent due to provide briefing on outcome to MW and PD  today.  Assuming positive feedback on IBM broader commercial deal to include CCA then plan for week of 11/28 is to engage GBS Delivery owner, John White,  Global Client Exec - Andrew Creasey to agree deal interlock for a December  close plan.  Commercial model and delivery plan shared with Julian as input to meeting at VPC.  Update on close plan will be provided on 11/28 once next steps clear.

11/18 A lot of activity this week.  Calls with Vodafone to validate approach, thoughts on contracting model and to ensure next steps are clear.  Matt working on commercial clarifications as agreed with Pedro and Samer and on target to deliver first pass on 11/21.
IBM engagement has also kicked off in ernest and some concerns flagged on both sides over IBM desire to have CS contract for any work with Vodafone on procurement on blue paper.  Various escalations initiated on IBM side however Pascal has control and we have a meeting planned with Julian Trent on 11/22 to work through details of joint engagement plan and contracting approach - primary concern at this point is for IBM not to place an excessive delivery overhead on our commercial proposal.  
Two more sessions planned with Vodafone but dates not yet set 1. Broader product and capability overview session 2. Insight lifecycle showcase to category managers - dates TBA


11/14 - Commercial call with Pedro and Samer to get Matt engaged and to develop a clear view of dependencies on moving the proposal forward.  A number of points raised and priority is to have a commercial model developed - and clearly broken down over Phases 1-3 that provides enough clarity for Pedro and Samer to present to procurement stakeholders and CIO.  Matt to develop model with input from Bob, Pascal and Sunil.
Immediate next step is meeting to address all open solution questions - scheduled for 11/16.
Delivery of commercial model TBA - target 11/21.
Objective is to provide Pedro and sponsors with adequate confidence to sign off Phase 1 - $100k SoW in December. This will however require confidence in the total technical and commercial proposition - there are some significant questions to address so a Q4 decision needs more qualification - pedro would not be pushed on timing for P1 sign off based on current position.

11/7 - Matt W to engage Pedro Barata by 11/11 to discuss next steps and for an update following Pedro's discussion with Virginie.  Pascal has taken action list for Cogscale review and follow up this week.

11/02 - Call with category management exec to review proposal, commercial structure and clarify i open questions.  VPC team to review internally with a view to follow up call week of 11/7 once Virginie Vast is back in the office.  Matt and Pascal to agree next steps. VPC decision making process needs careful navigation between stakeholders.


10/30 - Conference call arranged with Category management exec.  


10/27 - Finalise detailed proposal and continue discussions with Vfone commercial team


use case workshop, part 2, on 17-October.  Will then be prepared to propose 60-100k project for building out a "vision" prototype.

Hey Matt/Bob

Apologies this took a while - all a bit manic here at the moment.

As I explained to Matt, I need to pause everything (or at least the Turing Stylist project) for a few months, essentially whilst we regroup with the Babylone team and decide the direction for the front-end of the project.

Pru meeting is Jan 23rd and they require draft material from us by Jan 15th.

Matt will lead and qualify what can be done to meet the Jan 23rd showcase date.

(This could be an enterprise platform and Retirement services could start, but I could envision Wealth, corporate, etc using this too with their own solutions/apps);  we should have this discussion in the next week; Jean Acosta  can come to the NY CognitiveScale offices and we can dial in Karen and John – Monique, you’re welcome to join!
Set up a meeting within the next two to three weeks with PNC to have a workshop (how much time do we need?) where we’d:
Float the idea/proposal
Prioritize the use cases
Dig deep into the top one or two and obtain sufficient requirements so that we could build a potential model
Coordinate a PoC (we’d do this as part of the sales process as we know they’re looking at others, but if we come with a platform and specific solution, we might easily synch this deal)
 
Jean Acosta Microsoft will reach out to PNC in the next couple of days to get their availability.  Workshop will be held in person at PNC. Details must be shared with PNC. ( Ed to get details on workshop, time frame, agenda, who should attend from PNC side (backgrounds)……….

Action_Plan__c:
Officially Dead.  

Mid-January, we will regroup with Akshaya.  Of course, Akshaya is moving from CEO to adviser role for next six months.  

6-December.  Proposal presentation to CEO, Akshaya, scheduled for the afternoon.  Matt, Rich, Bob

13- Nov.  Manoj met with Akshaya.  BG had a chat with Manoj and summarized as follows

- no commitment to the 5M (yet)
- seemed to want to start with the CoC
- wants to drive "code" out every two weeks.  which sounds like the production line
- they have a 3-day offsite starting tomorrow.  He has asked for 35M from the board for the program (I don't know if that is one year or more).  
- Manoj stated that he wants more than a letter of intent (which is what Akshaya offered).  Told me I should speak to Pat and Bob Horn about this...not sure what good that is going to do as all Pat will want is SaaS contract.  

We need to remember that anything we build, that is licensed by the bank, is still subject to all the IT governance as it relates to security, privacy, data, etc.  Given there is no software even available yet, I have NO idea on how we would actually sign a SaaS deal. 



30-October.  Working on proposal for Manoj's meeting with Akshaya, scheduled for 14-November.  Have attached current thinking....work in progress.  hopefully have use cases confirmed on the 14th.  Major reorg underway as we work through this....

9-August.  Given state of product, readiness of security and BEAM/contracts, etc.  moving this out to end of year....sorry, no other choice and we are lucky the bank is moving slow

16-May.  Sourcing process incl of BEAM needs to complete by 31-May; contract review needs to complete this week and negotiations take place by mid-June. My gut says this is all at risk ({in terms of timing) as pilot date has now slipped to August and one could say they dont need the SaaS in place until then......

. Use case Insights for Finical Advisors also want to talk about Insights for prospecting for Financial Advisors

9/20- Draft Deck to review internal 

The use case we have been talking to him are the following. 

“My Wealth” -  (for the Client) 

CognitiveScale uses each Client’s personalized “Profile of One” to intelligently provide the most relevant market and portfolio insights across the Client’s journey. The journey starts from the initial on-boarding process and then provides ongoing/continuous service. 

An example might be to use a Dow Jones news feed, and to give intelligently selected relevant news.  

 “My Client” - (for the Financial Advisor)

Deliver intelligently personalized client insights to Advisors — this will help the Advisor to get a more complete view of the relevant financial landscape (which will vary by Client profile), and potentially to more efficiently share it across a larger Client base. 

This can promote trust and loyalty. e.g. “Reason to contact” “Auto To Do" list of contacts who you need to talk to today. 

“High Potential” - (for the Financial Advisor) 

This would intelligently identify the best potential clients based on their “Profile of One” and other factors, in order to contact them for possible upset or cross-sell — e.g. growth of funds or moving up to the next tier of service.

Name: LPL Financial - CCT Ent AI Phase2
Compelling_Events__c: CEO Quantum initiative has the goal of taking FA's on the LPL platform from 17K to 40K by 2022
Vision__c: Vision for this account is development into a highly strategic long term and commercially significant partnership driving $5M+ in ARR by JAN 2021
Current_Situation__c: Compliance, Legal & Risk (CLR) is positioning to transform internal operations to significantly reduce internal FTE cost while also creating a differentiating capability around cognitive automation
Action_Plan__c: 5/19/19 - Key to moving this opportunity forward will be successful close and delivery, with Capgemini, of Phase 1 (CCPA & Doc Tagging) within the Q2-Q3 timeframe, prior to their fall budgeting. This oppty is set for 12/31/19 close on the vision of incented execution within our Q4 with revenue realization beginning in 2020, against LPL budget allocated for 2020 in fall of 2019. Additionally and in parallel we need to support LPL in their internal efforts, following their 5/16 ASE Transformation Design session, with development of a Board credible Cognitive Capability Transformation Roadmap and Program Design. The amount here is a placeholder, pending further discovery, program design, value assessment and resourcing estimation, but is intended to be a conservative estimate of achievable potential revenue based on business vision as articulated in the ASE, and alignment with unique Cogscale capability.
Problems_Impacts__c: Gain Efficiency through RPA/IPA, reduce headcount in compliance by 400 by June 2019
Decision_Making_Process__c: Bob Rose will champion. This will likely be an Operating Comittee and Board level Transformation investment and Program.
